{"key":"processedPost-12754721","value":{"id":12754721,"first":12752490,"last":12758230,"when":1276740559,"utime":"06/17/10 05:09 AM","content":"<blockquote>Quote:<br /><b>BrandNewbie said:</b><br />If you're using a fluorescent light, it doesn't matter how far the light is from your substrate...<br /></blockquote><br /><br />Wrong.<br /><br />The intensity of light decreases by the square of the distance.&nbsp; If you move a light from 1' away from your substrate to 2' away, you only get 1/4 the light.<br /><br />As has been posted dozens of times in the last few weeks, you put the light as close as you can without causing excessive heat buildup in the growing area.<br />RR","title":"Re: how close to sub does light need to be?","forum":"Mushroom Cultivation"}}